and set up the hangings of the court gate,

00:15:50.540 --> 00:15:55.260
so Moses finished the work."

00:15:55.260 --> 00:15:56.820
We read these verses of Scripture

00:15:56.820 --> 00:16:00.299
and we see the obedience of Moses.

00:16:00.299 --> 00:16:03.779
We find that Moses was faithful

00:16:03.779 --> 00:16:06.540
to obey the commandment of the Lord.

00:16:06.540 --> 00:16:09.940
We've often mentioned over the course

00:16:09.940 --> 00:16:12.779
of many lessons in the book of Joshua

00:16:12.779 --> 00:16:15.059
that we've been studying during this pandemic

00:16:15.059 --> 00:16:17.019
and various messages throughout

00:16:17.059 --> 00:16:18.540
the last several weeks,

00:16:18.540 --> 00:16:21.059
even as we looked at the life of Ezra,

00:16:21.059 --> 00:16:23.540
that he prepared his heart to seek the law of the Lord

00:16:23.540 --> 00:16:25.619
and to do it, right?

00:16:25.619 --> 00:16:28.179
And to teach in Israel statutes and judgments.

00:16:28.179 --> 00:16:30.380
Ezra 7 and verse number 10.

00:16:30.380 --> 00:16:34.540
We find that there is throughout the Scripture,

00:16:34.540 --> 00:16:36.220
throughout the entirety of Scripture,

00:16:36.220 --> 00:16:40.260
there is an obvious importance

00:16:40.260 --> 00:16:43.500
that God places upon obedience.

00:16:43.500 --> 00:16:45.739
We sing trust and obey.

00:16:45.779 --> 00:16:48.579
We sing songs, I will obey.

00:16:48.579 --> 00:16:51.420
We talk about the importance of obedience.

00:16:51.420 --> 00:16:55.179
We talk about the fact that we're to be doers of the Word

00:16:55.179 --> 00:16:57.059
and not hearers only.

00:16:57.059 --> 00:16:58.739
Well, here, if we were to sum up

00:16:58.739 --> 00:17:02.179
that which is given to us in verses 16 through 33,

00:17:02.179 --> 00:17:04.220
we would simply be able to summarize

00:17:04.220 --> 00:17:06.540
these verses of Scripture by saying,

00:17:06.540 --> 00:17:08.660
Moses obeyed.

00:17:08.660 --> 00:17:10.540
He did what the Lord told him to do.

00:17:12.660 --> 00:17:15.299
We find that he was only able to obey

00:17:15.339 --> 00:17:17.820
because he had been given the instruction.

00:17:17.820 --> 00:17:20.140
God had faithfully given the instruction,

00:17:20.140 --> 00:17:24.100
but then it was up to Moses to obey that instruction.

00:17:24.100 --> 00:17:26.660
You know, as we look at the Word of God,

00:17:26.660 --> 00:17:29.260
we can say with certainty

00:17:29.260 --> 00:17:32.019
that God has given us His Word.

00:17:32.019 --> 00:17:34.500
We have the Word of God.

00:17:34.500 --> 00:17:35.820
It's one thing to have it.

00:17:35.820 --> 00:17:37.100
It's one thing to know it.

00:17:37.100 --> 00:17:40.660
It is entirely different to obey it.

00:17:40.660 --> 00:17:43.820
To be a doer of the Word.

00:17:43.820 --> 00:17:44.940
See, it's interesting.

00:17:44.940 --> 00:17:46.459
The passage of Scripture reminds me,

00:17:46.459 --> 00:17:47.380
when I think about obedience,

00:17:47.380 --> 00:17:49.299
it reminds me of a truth in John 2.

00:17:49.299 --> 00:17:50.739
Turn to the book of John, if you will,

00:17:50.739 --> 00:17:52.540
and look at the second chapter with me.

00:17:52.540 --> 00:17:54.220
And in John chapter number 2

00:17:54.220 --> 00:17:56.540
is the first miracle that's recorded

00:17:56.540 --> 00:17:58.700
in the life and ministry of the Lord Jesus Christ.

00:17:58.700 --> 00:18:01.059
It's the miracle at the marriage of Cana.

00:18:01.059 --> 00:18:03.019
We're familiar with that which takes place.

00:18:03.019 --> 00:18:06.339
And as we look at John chapter number 2,

00:18:06.339 --> 00:18:09.619
the Bible tells us as we begin the passage of Scripture

00:18:09.619 --> 00:18:11.299
that in the third day,

00:18:11.299 --> 00:18:12.980
there was a marriage in Cana of Galilee

00:18:13.019 --> 00:18:14.820
and the mother of Jesus was there.

00:18:14.820 --> 00:18:15.779
Notice in verse 2,

00:18:15.779 --> 00:18:19.260
and both Jesus was called and His disciples to the marriage.

00:18:19.260 --> 00:18:20.140
When they wanted wine,

00:18:20.140 --> 00:18:21.660
the mother of Jesus saith unto Him,

00:18:21.660 --> 00:18:23.100
they have no wine.

00:18:23.100 --> 00:18:24.220
Jesus saith unto her,

00:18:24.220 --> 00:18:25.779
Woman, what have I to do with thee?

00:18:25.779 --> 00:18:28.059
Mine hour is not yet come.

00:18:28.059 --> 00:18:30.059
It's interesting in this first miracle

00:18:30.059 --> 00:18:31.500
at the marriage of Cana,

00:18:31.500 --> 00:18:34.419
you begin to see this subject matter

00:18:34.419 --> 00:18:37.299
that runs throughout the entirety of the book of John

00:18:37.299 --> 00:18:39.419
with regard to the hour.

00:18:39.419 --> 00:18:41.659
And Jesus would often refer to the fact

00:18:41.659 --> 00:18:42.900
that the hour has not come

00:18:42.900 --> 00:18:43.739
and He says,

00:18:43.739 --> 00:18:45.820
Mine hour is not yet come.

00:18:45.820 --> 00:18:47.059
He understood the purpose

00:18:47.059 --> 00:18:49.260
in which He had come to this sin-cursed world.

00:18:49.260 --> 00:18:52.179
He understood that He would live a perfect sinless life,

00:18:52.179 --> 00:18:54.059
that He would go to the cross of Calvary

00:18:54.059 --> 00:18:55.460
to pay for the sin of the world,

00:18:55.460 --> 00:18:57.099
that He would be buried in a borrowed tomb

00:18:57.099 --> 00:18:59.619
and that He would rise in victory on the third day,

00:18:59.619 --> 00:19:01.820
conquering sin, death and the grave.

00:19:01.820 --> 00:19:03.940
It's not until John chapter number 17

00:19:03.940 --> 00:19:06.020
that you read where Jesus says,

00:19:06.020 --> 00:19:08.460
Mine hour is come.

00:19:08.460 --> 00:19:09.659
There are many references

00:19:09.659 --> 00:19:11.419
between John 2 and John 17

00:19:11.460 --> 00:19:13.179
of the hour,

00:19:13.179 --> 00:19:16.099
but it's not until that time in John 17

00:19:16.099 --> 00:19:17.539
that Jesus says,

00:19:17.539 --> 00:19:19.340
Mine hour is come.

00:19:19.340 --> 00:19:21.859
But notice this truth in John chapter number two

00:19:21.859 --> 00:19:23.219
in verse number five.

00:19:23.219 --> 00:19:26.539
Notice what Mary says to these servants.

00:19:26.539 --> 00:19:28.700
His mother saith unto the servants,

00:19:28.700 --> 00:19:29.859
notice this,

00:19:30.859 --> 00:19:35.580
whatsoever he saith unto you, do it.

00:19:35.580 --> 00:19:37.099
I like that verse.

00:19:38.099 --> 00:19:42.619
The mother of Jesus, Mary,

00:19:42.619 --> 00:19:46.419
she says to Jesus about the problem

00:19:46.419 --> 00:19:49.539
in verse number three,

00:19:49.539 --> 00:19:50.380
she saith unto him,

00:19:50.380 --> 00:19:51.219
they have no wine.

00:19:51.219 --> 00:19:54.299
And we find that the mother, Mary,

00:19:54.299 --> 00:19:56.739
now turns to these servants

00:19:56.739 --> 00:19:58.820
and she says to the servants,

00:19:58.820 --> 00:20:00.419
whatsoever he saith.

00:20:00.419 --> 00:20:07.859
He saith unto you, do it.

00:20:07.859 --> 00:20:09.659
See, I remember hearing this phrase

00:20:09.659 --> 00:20:11.139
when I was young.

00:20:11.139 --> 00:20:14.179
Yours is not to reason why.

00:20:14.179 --> 00:20:15.599
Just to do or die.

00:20:15.599 --> 00:20:18.459
Some of us are familiar with that phraseology.

00:20:18.459 --> 00:20:20.339
And I believe, I guess,

00:20:20.339 --> 00:20:22.499
from at least my perspective,

00:20:22.499 --> 00:20:24.859
I never have researched it,

00:20:24.859 --> 00:20:27.019
but in my mind, contextually,

00:20:27.019 --> 00:20:29.259
it's a military thing.

00:20:29.259 --> 00:20:30.739
You don't need to question why.

00:20:30.739 --> 00:20:31.819
Yours isn't to reason why.

00:20:31.819 --> 00:20:32.939
It's just to do or die.

00:20:32.939 --> 00:20:37.479
Just do it because I said kind of a situation.

00:20:37.479 --> 00:20:38.939
You know, the reality when we come

00:20:38.939 --> 00:20:41.539
to the commandments of the Lord,

00:20:41.539 --> 00:20:45.259
that's absolutely how our response should be.

00:20:45.259 --> 00:20:46.799
Just do it.

00:20:46.799 --> 00:20:50.979
Whatsoever He saith unto you, do it.

00:20:50.979 --> 00:20:53.419
You think about the miracle there in John 2,

00:20:53.419 --> 00:20:55.059
and you think about what happens.

00:20:55.059 --> 00:20:56.459
It's interesting, we don't have time

00:20:56.459 --> 00:20:57.659
to go through the entirety.

00:20:57.659 --> 00:20:59.219
It's not really the subject matter

00:20:59.219 --> 00:21:00.299
by which we're studying,

00:21:00.299 --> 00:21:03.019
but we find that what was the instruction

00:21:03.019 --> 00:21:04.539
that Jesus gave,

00:21:04.539 --> 00:21:07.979
fill the water pots with water.

00:21:07.979 --> 00:21:10.579
And the Bible just simply says in v. 7,

00:21:10.579 --> 00:21:13.499
and they filled them up to the brim.

00:21:13.499 --> 00:21:14.859
They didn't question.

00:21:14.859 --> 00:21:16.699
They didn't have some long debate

00:21:16.699 --> 00:21:19.219
